<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yildirim" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Galium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Galium shinasii" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="shinasii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Galium shinasii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a endemic for Eastern Anatolia. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="It’s">It's</normalizedToken>
known that is from Levent Canyon (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Known distribution of: Galium shinasii (✹), Galium cornigerum (▲), Galium sorgerae (●), Galium lasiocarpum (■)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.75.10244.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/112896" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">5</figureCitation>
) in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Akçadağ">Akcadag</normalizedToken>
district, and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Eskiköy">Eskikoey</normalizedToken>
in 
<pageBreakToken pageId="5" pageNumber="24" start="start">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Doğanşehir">Dogansehir</normalizedToken>
</pageBreakToken>
district in Malatya province and near Refahiye district in Erzincan (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Known distribution of: Galium shinasii (✹), Galium cornigerum (▲), Galium sorgerae (●), Galium lasiocarpum (■)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.75.10244.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/112896" pageId="5" pageNumber="24">5</figureCitation>
). It is an element belonging to the Irano-Turanian floristic region and colonizes only marlstone-calcareous cliffs, usually those with an eastern and south-eastern orientation, at an elevation of 1200-1800 m. It is an obligate chasmophyte.
</paragraph>
